1 - Build project
-----------------

You should use Apache Maven version 3 or more to build project.
Maven can be found at https://maven.apache.org/

To build projects use : 

$> mvn clean package -DskipTests=true 

Projects can be found in target dirs. 

3 - Start embedded Tomcat for development
------------------------------------------

Start integrated server

$> ./run.sh or mvn install -P run

Refer also to Alfresco Maven SDK 2.0

2 - Run Tests
--------------

To run all Junit tests :

$> mvn clean test -Dmaven.test.failure.ignore=true -P purge

To run specific test

$> mvn test -Dtest=MyTest.java -DfailIfNoTests=false

Integrations tests require beCPG server to be launch first.

In other console:

$> ./run.sh or mvn install -P run

3 - Deploy projects
-------------------

Refer to INSTALL

4 - Translate projects
---------------------

Create an account to 

https://translate.zanata.org/zanata/project/view/becpg

and submit your translations
